Friday Olokor, Abuja The timetable for the engagement of stakeholders for the collection of Permanent Voter Cards and other activities would be out in the next few days, the Independent National Electoral Commission, has said. The items, the commission said, would be needed for the November 16 governorship elections in Kogi and Bayelsa States. INEC National Commissioner and Chairman, Information and Voter Education Committee, Festus Okoye, according to the commission’s bulletin Volume 2 N0: 085, gave the hint in Abuja while declaring open a two-day national strategy meeting on “Capturing disaggregated data of Persons with Disabilities”, organised with support from the International Foundation for Electoral Systems. He said, “In the next few days, the commission will announce the time table for stakeholders’ engagement for PVC collection and other activities relating to the states where we are going to have standalone governorship elections and the issue of this data collection will be one of the big issues in relation to whether we conduct good elections in Bayelsa and Kogi States.” 